        * Outlook Click-To-Run version 2108 (build 14326.20258) or later is required
      </div>
      <h4>Installation</h4>
      <p>To allow your users to apply signatures using the Outlook Add-in please install the add-in through the Exchange Admin Center.</p>
      <p>Full installation instructions can be found <a href="https://support.portal.exclaimer.com/hc/en-gb/articles/360020741398">here</a></p>
      <p>If you are using the older Manifest file, please see the guide <a href="https://support.portal.exclaimer.com/hc/en-gb/articles/6420946508829-Migrate-Exclaimer-Cloud-Outlook-Add-in-from-Manifest-to-App-Store">here</a> on how to migrate to the new App Store release</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cp-container-body-item">
      <h3 class="desktopagent-windows">Desktop Agent (Windows)</h3>
      <h4>Suitable For</h4>
      <p>Desktop Outlook on Windows machines only.</p>
      <p>Individual or 'All Users' machine deployment via local MSI installation, CMD Script or Group
        Policy.</p>
      <h4>Version</h4>
      <p>1.18.22294.00001</p>
      <h4>Requirements</h4>
      <table>
        <tr>
          <td style="width:33%;">Software:</td>
          <td>
            <ol>
              <li>Windows 8.1 or above</li>
              <li>Outlook 2013 or above</li>
              <li>.NET Framework 4.6.2 or above</li>
            </ol>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Permissions (Per User):</td>
          <td>
            <ol>
              <li>Local Installation Rights</li>
            </ol>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Permissions (All Users):</td>
          <td>
            <ol>
              <li>Domain Administrator (MSI Only)</li>
            </ol>
          </td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <div class="cp-download">
        <a aria-role="button" class="cp-btn" href="https://outlookclient.exclaimer.net/csua/Exclaimer.CloudSignatureAgent.application">Download Click-Once ></a>
        <a aria-role="button" class="cp-btn" href="https://outlookclient.exclaimer.net/csua/Exclaimer.CloudSignatureUpdateAgent.Install.msi">Download MSI ></a>
      </div>
      <h4>Installation</h4>
      <p>To install the Outlook Signatures Update Agent, please click on the "Download for Windows" button. Once downloaded, the installation will begin. Once the agent is installed, you will be prompted to sign in to Office 365 to grant permissions for the agent. Any signatures assigned to you will then automatically be downloaded for you to use in Outlook.</p>
			<p>If you are an administrator who would like to install the agent via GPO, then you can download the MSI package for the Outlook Signature Update Agent, using <a href="https://outlookclient.exclaimer.net/csua/Exclaimer.CloudSignatureUpdateAgent.Install.msi">this link</a>. For help installing via GPO please see our KB <a href="https://go.exclaimer.com/209">here</a></p>
    </div>
