      <h3 class="desktopagent-mac">Desktop Agent (macOS)</h3>
      <h4>Suitable For</h4>
      <p>Desktop Outlook for Mac or Apple Mail only.</p>
      <p>Individual deployment via local machine installation, or deployed via Intune.</p>
      <h4>Version</h4>
      <p>1.1.0.83</p>
      <h4>Requirements</h4>
      <table>
        <tr>
          <td style="width:33%;">Software:</td>
          <td>
            <ol>
              <li>macOS 10.13 or above</li>
              <li>Office for macOS</li>
              <li>Rosetta 2 (M1/M2 CPUs)</li>
            </ol>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Permissions (Per User):</td>
          <td>
            <ol>
              <li>Local Installation Rights</li>
              <li>Full Disk Access</li>
            </ol>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Permissions (All Users):</td>
          <td>
            <ol>
              <li>Microsoft 365 Admin (Intune)</li>
              <li>Full Disk Access</li>
            </ol>
          </td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <a aria-role="button" class="cp-btn" href="https://outlookclient.exclaimer.net/csua/Exclaimer%20Signature%20Agent-1.1.0.83.dmg">Download for macOS ></a>
      <h4>Installation</h4>
      <p>To install the Exclaimer Signature Agent, please click on the "Download for macOS" button. Once downloaded, mount the .dmg file, then run the .pkg installer to install the agent. Once the agent is installed, you will be prompted to sign in to Office 365 to grant permissions for the agent. Any signatures assigned to you will then automatically be downloaded for you to use in Outlook and Apple Mail.</p>
      <p>If you are an administrator who would like to install the agent across a network, then you can use the .pkg installer with your administration software.</p>
